85
00:04:04,240 --> 00:04:07,300
Scott: Why would you rage quit in a game that is, like, 30 seconds long?

86
00:04:07,320 --> 00:04:07,989
Scott: You wanna know why?

87
00:04:08,010 --> 00:04:08,760
Rym: I'll tell you why.

88
00:04:08,821 --> 00:04:10,300
Scott: Does it have a record, like Mario Kart?

89
00:04:10,863 --> 00:04:10,903
Scott: No.

90
00:04:10,923 --> 00:04:11,710
Rym: There's no record.

91
00:04:11,730 --> 00:04:13,000
Scott: You have no idea how good people are.

92
00:04:13,000 --> 00:04:16,240
Scott: So you're not even hurting yourself in any way, versus losing.

93
00:04:16,481 --> 00:04:16,562
Rym: Zero.

94
00:04:16,582 --> 00:04:18,240
Rym: So here's why people rage quit.

95
00:04:18,680 --> 00:04:24,000
Rym: The way it works is, you're basically, whoever's player one picks the map, and when you both hit ready, you just fight.

96
00:04:24,560 --> 00:04:29,015
Rym: The only information you get, unless you chat with each other, is the name.

97
00:04:29,075 --> 00:04:30,500
Rym: Like, the Steam name.

98
00:04:31,300 --> 00:04:40,400
Rym: So, what'll happen is, someone will be playing against me, and I trounce them, and then, once you beat someone, you play the same person again, if you want, most of the time.

99
00:04:41,025 --> 00:04:42,899
Rym: So, they'll join the game again.

100
00:04:43,080 --> 00:04:43,697
Scott: They see it's you.

101
00:04:43,960 --> 00:04:47,280
Rym: They see me trouncing them, and they quit, hoping to get another player.

102
00:04:47,660 --> 00:04:50,340
Rym: But there aren't other players, because I've already driven everyone else away.

103
00:04:50,921 --> 00:04:56,480
Rym: So the ready room reappears, it's just me, and then the same name that just rage quit joins again.

104
00:04:57,221 --> 00:05:00,000
Rym: And then immediately rage quits once they recognize my name.

105
